ranked_diseases.explanation: Strong match with intellectual disability, developmental delay, hypertelorism, thick eyebrows, bulbous nose, long philtrum, and delayed speech. Macrodontia is also a recognized feature. KMT2D mutations cause this syndrome.
X-linked form caused by KDM6A mutations. Similar features to Kabuki syndrome 1 but less common. Compatible with male patient and similar facial dysmorphisms.
Features thick eyebrows, bulbous nose, intellectual disability, and developmental delays. However, typically includes more severe hand/foot abnormalities not mentioned in this patient.
Presents with intellectual disability, thick eyebrows, hypertelorism, and developmental delays. Caused by KMT2A mutations. Dental abnormalities can occur.
Features intellectual disability, thick eyebrows, long philtrum, and developmental delays. However, typically includes limb abnormalities and more severe growth restriction.
Can present with intellectual disability, bulbous nose, and speech delays. However, typically includes short stature and triangular face which aren't mentioned.
